The paper deals with structured light-based range imaging, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of color stripes and the need to handle surface discontinuities suggest that the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also presents methods for reducing the influence of object colors, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications.
